			<summary>Feeling Responsive allows you to use all kinds of headers. This example shows a header image with a defined background color via front matter.</summary>
			<content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/feeling-responsive/design/header-image-color/">&lt;p&gt;It’s so easy to do. Just define in front matter an image and a background color. Instead of a color you can also use a pattern image. Have a look at the &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:4000/feeling-responsive/design/header-image-pattern/&quot;&gt;example with a background pattern&lt;/a&gt;.
